order to run this ministry even more efficiently so we can focus on what is important. These partners have truly been great, so I would like to point them out and tell you a bit about them.</p><p><h3><a href="http://buildit.sitesell.com/azavia.html" target="_blank">Site Build It! Your Path to a Successful Online Business</a></h3></p><p>In August, 2010, Christine and I started what was then called The Full Effect. Our dream was to create a ministry that would bring healing to others.</p><p>Since then, the vision has grown and improved into what it is today, <a href="http://www.christs-light-ministries.org/"><strong>Christ's Light Ministries</strong></a>.</p><p>When I began <strong>Christ's Light Ministries</strong>, I wanted to ensure that it was successful. The Full Effect had meager success, and I just didn't have the knowledge or resources to market it properly. We got some visitors, but they were mostly spammers.</p><p>So, with the renewed vision, i wanted a renewed effort to make it succeed. Of course, I trusted in God to help us, but I knew that I had to do something on my end, too.</p><p>Sure enough, God started to put <a href="http://buildit.sitesell.com/azavia.html">Site Build It!</a> in our path. I had come across it a few years back, but in my pride of being an accomplished programmer, dismissed it as a solution only for beginners to the Web.</p><p>But now, I took a fresh look at it, recognizing my own ignorance of marketing, search engine optimization, etc. This solution claimed to do all of that for me, and more.</p><p>So, I took the tentative step of signing up for <a href="http://buildit.sitesell.com/azavia.html">Site Build It!</a> on April 29, and officially launched the site on May 1, after reading through their very detailed Action Guide, which gave me all the steps to creating a successful Web site.</p><p>They emphasize that the important part was to create new, unique, and engaging content for my Web site, which I have done ever since, having now over 300-400 pages. It would take care of the rest, and teach me to do my part, too.</p><p>And, <a href="http://buildit.sitesell.com/azavia.html">Site Build It!</a> has certainly delivered. It has only been a month and a half, but here are our statistics for June 22, 2011:</p><p><dl><dt>Visits</dt><dd>474</dd><dt>Unique Visitors</dt><dd>268</dt><dt>Page Views</dt><dd>1,127</dd></dl></p><p>This is only after about a month and a half, and it is growing steadily. Meanwhile, others I have spoken to have only received 50-100 visitors a day even six months after starting.</p><p>We've already received many customers, and people who participate in the <a href="http://www.christs-light-ministries.org/spiritual-forums.html">forums</a>. I've had more clients now than I ever have, and people seem to love the Web site.</p><p>But, I can honestly say that I couldn't have had nearly this success if it weren't for <a href="http://buildit.sitesell.com/azavia.html">Site Build It!</a></p><p><h3><a href="http://www.bigcommerce.com/3820.html">BigCommerce: Get Your Store Up in Minutes</a></h3></p><p>I just signed up for <a href="http://www.bigcommerce.com/3820.html">BigCommerce</a> recently, but already it has been great.</p><p>I had been looking for a good solution for my store. I tried Amazon Web Store, but it was inaccessible to my screen reader, so that was out the window. I explored some other solutions, and finally landed on <a href="http://www.bigcommerce.com/3820.html">BigCommerce</a>.</p><p>I had a database of all of our products, but no way to upload them until then. However, with <a href="http://www.bigcommerce.com/3820.html">BigCommerce</a>, I was able to upload my products in a simple and flexible format. I added hundreds of products in a matter of minutes, while I was adding one at a time before.</p><p>There are so many features that I like, that it is hard to know where to start.</p><p>They firstly integrate with many payment gateways, and even have their own gateway that allows you to accept credit cards, if you have a business checking account. I got signed up with that right away, and am accepting PayPal as well.</p><p>The Web interface is very flexible, but the default is very nice as well, which I like so that I don't have to get a designer involved, which costs more money, of course.</p><p>In every way, it just feels like a big retail store, but really <a href="http://www.bigcommerce.com/3820.html">BigCommerce</a> is not that expensive at all.</p><p>They have so many marketing tools, all of which are great. My favorites so far are the integration with Google Products, and especially the ability to post products to eBay and keep track of the listings. You just create listing templates with all of the specifications for the listings, and then post all the products you want.</p><p>They also have an e-mail marketing section with integration with several services, including iContact and others. I have not explored these options yet, but it looks very promising.</p><p>It has great handling of shipping, shipping methods and calculations. You can either select to calculate quotes in real time, or set your own rules for shipping prices.</p><p>It has the most robust handling for taxes that I have ever seen before, so it will handle just about any problem you can throw at it.</p><p>Finally, there are wonderful features for discounts and coupons, which are very flexible. You can create discounts for anything you like and according to any conditions.</p><p>They of course handle all of the search engine optimization, though it is strongly suggested that you take advantage of the fields for keywords and descriptions under each page, category and product to make it even better.</p><p>I've only just begun with this store, so I don't have any stats, but I truly believe that it will be just as successful as the main site has been, if not more so.</p><p><hr align="left" width="100%"